<br>
Or is it only when the hint of accusation arises from me saying &quot;I'm learning to let go of past hurts&quot; hits you right in your manipulative self-deceiving tiny little heart that you feel so defensive?  That I tell you I needed you and you tell me I was never there for you?  Me?! the child who came running to you in tears only to be laughed at once she felt safe in doing so.<br>
<br>
You know what?  Go right ahead.  Make innuendo that I'm not as great a parent as you are a grandparent.  Suggest and hint that your capacity to love is greater than mine.  Paint me with your tainted brush.  Go on! no really, do it!  You know why?<br>
<br>
Because for the last time I put my mind to this to give myself back power that I should have never lost.<br>
<br>
You will NOT hold me victim to your own sense of how the world has wronged you.<br>
<br>
I will NOT apologize for being young and passionate and living life with every ounce of being a tiny soul possesses, unapologetically vicous in the appreciation of every breath and ray of sunshine, blade of grass and stroke of flesh on flesh.<br>
<br>
Nor will I expect you to apologize for having complimented me with left hand while right hand was slapping my face, and for having shat all over every single one of my dreams and what I found beautiful in the world.<br>
<br>
For the last time I tell myself this is it - You are who you are, hurt angered flawed and I cannot change that, have no right to and will gain nothing for it if I could.<br>
<br>
This right here is the line.  <br>
<br>
I will continue to speak respectfully to you.  I will continue to do what a good child does.  I will stop thinking the bitter thoughts because you are so wrapped up in yourself, in your own perception of the world, in your obligation to uphold the wounded image, the one who loves and gives of herself and no one understands.  This is my final gift to you, I forgive you.  I forgive you for hating me because you hated yourself.  And I forgive myself for hating you because you acted like such a miserable bitch to me.  And I am NOT hurt, will NOT allow myself to be hurt anymore.  I will burn this out of my soul once and for all and I will be better for it.  And I well and truly hope you come to a point in this existance or any others to follow, where your soul has found peace and happiness and is released from its torment, because there is beauty and divine in us all and we all deserve it. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://irianna.onethisway.com/sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
