<br>
I'm older then you and should be over it by now.  I have been self-destructive for over 20 years now.  I have had good periods like when I completed college despite my mothers efforts to even undermine that.  I have good jobs, but then I go downhill again.  I feel cheated and I see people with stable homes or parents who love them and provide for them and I get a very self-pity thing going.  It is not fair ya know .. that sort of thing.<br>
<br>
I have never had any help and everything I have managed to accomplish I had to eek it out myself and sometimes I just say I'm tired, but I think alot of it is resentment ... resentment my parents aren't there for me and never were and that other people have that and don't appreciate it.  How do you get past the feelings that you deserve better and your children certainly deserve better? I mean how nice it would be to have grandparents who actually care and help with my child or at least show love and affection for him?  He will never know that and it simply isn't fair to him.  He didn't ask to be unloved while seeing his friends have love .. I didn't ask for it.<br>
<br>
